ENTRY            E2395   20260116   20260227   20260227       E156
SUBENT        E2395001   20260116   20260227   20260227       E156
BIB                 12         34
TITLE      Production of 67Ga by alpha bombardment of natural
           zinc
AUTHOR     (Y.Nagame, M.Unno, H.Nakahara, Y.Murakami)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNTMU)
REFERENCE  (J,ARI,29,615,1978)
           Main reference. See also TITLE and AUTHOR.
           (J,RI,27,631,1978)
           3He-induced and part of alpha-induced reactions
INC-SOURCE Beam intensity is 0.5 uA.
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
           - Target-thickness is about 13 mg/cm2.
           - Target is self supported.
METHOD     (ACTIV) irradiated for 30 min. and 5 min. for
                   radioisotopes of long and short half lives,
                   respectively
           (STTA)
           (GSPEC)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2JPNIPC) No. 2 course.
DETECTOR   (GELI) 40cc Ge(Li) detector with 2048 channels to
                  detect decaying gamma-ray.
ERR-ANALYS The estimated cross section error is at least 15%
           excluding the uncertainty associated with photon
           intensities.
COMMENT    By author: The thick target yields are given in terms
           of microcuries of the activities produced by a 1-h
           irradiation of a natural zinc target with the beam
           current of 1 uA. (copied from B0135.001)
HISTORY    (20121211C) Tk
           (20260113T) MA: Subentries 012-023 moved from EXFOR
                       B0135. Main reference in 001 replaced.
                       STATUS in 002-023 and ANALYSIS in 007-011
                       updated. REACTION in 008-009 modified.
                       DECAY-DATA in 002-011 updated/added.
ENDBIB              34
